The paper focuses on enhancing the security and performance of Bitcoin through a novel Byzantine consensus protocol, which involves distributed systems, cryptography, and networking. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CR (Cryptography and Security), followed by cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing), cs.Distributed (Distributed Computing), cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture), and cs.SY (Systems and Control).
